p |date=8 June 2011 }}</ref>\n* [[Long Island Museum of American Art, History, and Carriages|The Long Island Museum of American Art, History & Carriages]], Stony Brook, New York\n* [[Pioneer Village (Utah)#Carriage Hall|Pioneer Village, Farmington, Utah.]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.farmingtonstar.com/carriagehall.html|title=Carriage Hall|publisher=|accessdate=12 February 2019}}</ref>\n* Thrasher Carriage Museum, Frostburg, Maryland<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hugedomains.com/domain_profile.cfm?d=thrashercarriage&e=com|title=HugeDomains.com - ThrasherCarriage.com is for sale (Thrasher Carriage)|website=www.hugedomains.com|accessdate=12 February 2019}}</ref>\n* [[Sylvanus Wade House|The Wesley W. Jung Carriage Museum]], Greenbush, Wisconsin<ref>{{cite web|url=https://wadehouse.wisconsinhistory.org/|title=Wade House - Wisconsin Historical Society - Home|website=Wade House|accessdate=12 February 2019}}</ref>\n* [[Shelburne Museum]], Shelburne, Vermont\n* Forney Museum of Transportation, Denver, Colorado<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.forneymuseum.org/|title=Forney Museum of Transportation|website=www.forneymuseum.org|accessdate=12 February 2019}}</ref>\n* Mifflinburg Buggy Museum, Mifflinburg, PA.  Only museum in US that preserves an original intact 19th century carriage factory.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.buggymuseum.org/|title=Mifflinburg Buggy Museum|website=www.buggymuseum.org|accessdate=12 February 2019}}</ref>\n* [[Frick Art & Historical Center]] Car & Carriage Museum, [[Pittsburgh]], Pennsylvania, preserving carriages owned by [[Henry Clay Frick]] and his family.<ref>[http://www.thefrickpgh.com The Frick Pittsburgh]</ref>\n\n==See also==\n{{div col|colwidth=22em}}\n* [[Horse-drawn vehicle]]\n* [[Horsecar]]\n* [[Horse harness]]\n* [[Driving (horse)]]\n* [[Horseless carriage]] (term for early automobiles)\n* [[Howdah]] (carriage positioned on the back of an elephant or camel)\n* [[Wagon]]\n* [[War wagon]]\n{{div col end}}\n\n==Notes==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==Fur